 best practices.  Contribute to internal training initiatives to enhance team knowledge and technical expertise. Customer Advocacy Act as the technical point of contact for customers during their pre-sales journey, ensuring their success and satisfaction.  Gather customer requirements and work closely with product and engineering teams to align solutions to customer needs.  Foster long-term relationships with prospects and customers, positioning Akamai as a strategic partner. Evangelism And Enablement Present Akamai’s API security vision and best practices at industry conferences, webinars, and customer workshops.  Create and maintain high-quality solution design documentation, presentations, and other technical sales assets.  Stay ahead of trends in API security, contributing to internal knowledge sharing and external thought leadership. Collaboration Across Teams Partner with sales, product management, and engineering teams to drive alignment and continuously improve the customer experience.  Support RFP responses with clear, concise, and accurate technical insights.  What We’re Looking For  Technical Expertise:  Strong knowledge of APIs, API gateways, web application firewalls (WAF), and API security practices.  Proficiency in internet technologies, including TCP/IP, DNS, HTTP/HTTPS, SSL/TLS, and RESTful APIs.  Hands-on experience with scripting languages such as Python, JavaScript, or Bash. Cloud And Kubernetes Experience Familiarity with cloud infrastructure (AWS, Azure, GCP) and cloud-native architectures.  Experience deploying and managing Kubernetes clusters and containerized applications.  Familiarity with Kubernetes networking, ingress controllers, and service mesh technologies (e.g., Istio, NGINX). Experience 3+ years in a technical pre-sales, solution architecture, or related role in cybersecurity or API-related fields.  Proven track record of designing and presenting technical solutions to customers and stakeholders. Communication Skills Exceptional presentation skills with the ability to explain complex concepts clearly to both technical and non-technical audiences.  Strong written communication skills, including email correspondence, technical documentation, and RFP responses. Problem-Solving And Collaboration Proven ability to analyze customer challenges and creatively design tailored solutions.  Collaborative mindset, working effectively across sales, product, and engineering teams. Nice-to-Have Qualifications Experience in vulnerability management, penetration testing, or incident response.  Knowledge of regulatory requirements such as PCI DSS, GDPR, APPI and SOC-2.  Certifications in relevant technologies or familiarity with OWASP API Top 10.  Familiarity with DevOps practices and tools (e.g., CI/CD pipelines, Helm, Terraform).  Why Join Akamai? At Akamai, you’ll join a collaborative and innovative team dedicated to solving some of the most pressing cybersecurity challenges facing enterprises today. You’ll have the opportunity to work with industry-leading solutions, engage with high-profile customers, and grow as a thought leader in API security.You’ll also play a key role in empowering your colleagues, acting as a subject matter expert on API security to ensure that the entire team stays ahead of evolving threats and technologies."}
